37#include <sys/cdefs.h>
38#ifndef lint
39__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-carp.c,v 1.3 2017/02/05 04:05:05 spz Exp $");
40#endif
41
42/* \summary: Common Address Redundancy Protocol (CARP) printer */
43
44#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
45#include "config.h"
46#endif
47
48#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
49
50#include "netdissect.h" /* for checksum structure and functions */
51#include "extract.h"
52
53void
54carp_print(netdissect_options *ndo, register const u_char *bp, register u_int len, int ttl)
55{
56 int version, type;
57 const char *type_s;
58
59 ND_TCHECK(bp[0]);
60 version = (bp[0] & 0xf0) >> 4;
61 type = bp[0] & 0x0f;
62 if (type == 1)
63 type_s = "advertise";
64 else
65 type_s = "unknown";
66 ND_PRINT((ndo, "CARPv%d-%s %d: ", version, type_s, len));
67 if (ttl != 255)
68 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[ttl=%d!] ", ttl));
69 if (version != 2 || type != 1)
70 return;
71 ND_TCHECK(bp[2]);
72 ND_TCHECK(bp[5]);
73 ND_PRINT((ndo, "vhid=%d advbase=%d advskew=%d authlen=%d ",
74 bp[1], bp[5], bp[2], bp[3]));
75 if (ndo->ndo_vflag) {
76 struct cksum_vec vec[1];
77 vec[0].ptr = (const uint8_t *)bp;
78 vec[0].len = len;
79 if (ND_TTEST2(bp[0], len) && in_cksum(vec, 1))
80 ND_PRINT((ndo, " (bad carp cksum %x!)",
81 EXTRACT_16BITS(&bp[6])));
82 }
83 ND_PRINT((ndo, "counter=%" PRIu64, EXTRACT_64BITS(&bp[8])));
84
85 return;
86trunc:
87 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|carp]"));
88}
